article.description: Sam Quigley scored 17 and No. 25 DePaul beat West Virginia 74-56 on Saturday night.
article.headline: DePaul goes on 17-5 run in second half to put West Virginia away
article.linkText: Quigley leads No. 25 DePaul to 4th straight win
article.story:
CHICAGO -- Sam Quigley scored 17 and No. 25 DePaul beat West Virginia 74-56 on Saturday night.

Felicia Chester and Natasha Williams both added 14 points as the Blue Demons (17-5, 5-3 Big East) won their fourth straight. DePaul's leading scorer Deirdre Naughton was ill and didn't play.

Liz Repella scored 19 to lead the Mountaineers (12-8, 1-6). Takisha Granberry added 15, her 13th straight game in double figures, and Sarah Miles had 10 as West Virginia lost for the sixth time in eight games.

The Blue Demons closed the game on a 13-6 run and hit 9-of-10 free throws in the final three minutes.

West Virginia hit five 3's to start the second half to draw within two, but DePaul responded with a 17-5 run to take a 61-47 lead with 5:53 left and put the game away.
